# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# FTP Server Configuration (Optional)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# NASA CDDIS FTP Authentication Email (OPTIONAL)
#
# canvod-aux uses a two-tier FTP server strategy:
#
# 1. PRIMARY SERVER (ESA): ftp://gssc.esa.int/gnss
#    - No authentication required
#    - Works out-of-the-box without any configuration
#    - Default for all auxiliary GNSS data downloads
#
# 2. FALLBACK SERVER (NASA CDDIS): ftp://gdc.cddis.eosdis.nasa.gov
#    - Requires user registration and email authentication
#    - Automatically enabled when CDDIS_MAIL is set
#    - Used as fallback if ESA server is unavailable
#
# To enable NASA CDDIS fallback:
# 1. Register for a free account at: https://urs.earthdata.nasa.gov/users/new
# 2. Uncomment the line below and replace with your registered email
# 3. Restart your application to apply changes
#
# If CDDIS_MAIL is not set:
# - Application will use ESA exclusively (perfectly fine for most use cases)
# - No authentication required
# - NASA CDDIS will be skipped from fallback attempts
#
# CDDIS_MAIL=your.email@example.com
